snippet: Lara Gut of Switzerland won a super-G in Lake Louise, Alberta, by three-hundredths of a second for her fourth victory in a World Cup season that is only eight races old.
abstract: Swiss skier Lara Gut wins super-G event in Lake Louise, Alberta, by three-hundredths of a second for her fourth victory in a World Cup season that is only eight races old.

headline.main: Swiss Wins Super-G Again and Vonn Is Fifth
